article.headline: Oral Roberts 83, Centenary 57
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 26 points to lead Oral Roberts past Centenary 83-57 Thursday night. Green was 8-of-11 from the field and 10-of-11 from the free-throw line for the Golden Eagles (17-11, 12-3 Mid-Continent). Ken Tutt added 16 points, Larry Owens had 13 and Chris Riouse had 12, all 3-pointers. Chris Watson led the Gents (4-23, 2-14) with 16 points and Xavier Burnette added 11. Oral Roberts led 38-20 at the half and kept their post-season hopes alive with the win. The loss put an end to Centenary's season. Head coach Rob Flaska finished his debut season with a 4-23 overall mark, which included a 2-14 record within the conference.
